Doctors said 6 months to 1 year..

The will to win everyday…it’s been 2 months n half. 

I look in the mirror every single day and know I am doing everything possible to get better. 

That’s what success is about right?

I can relate my injuries to business, and working out. 

Each one requires a level of focus, purity, honesty & authenticity. 

Most importantly God. 

I’m realizing God prepared me for this already.. 

Is it easy ? No. 

Is it over yet? No, I have a journey ahead of me to get stronger. 

This journey has been .. 

a test of mental strength 

A test of perspective 

A test of self love 

A test of will 

A test of gratitude 

I’m becoming tougher, stronger, grittier and more impactful version of myself. 

I’m walking baby! 

I hope this gives someone else Strength to pull through their situation. Just don’t give up! We are in a battle daily with life.

Your timing is your timing.

It will happen.

Since my accident I’ve had to change everything about my workouts. 

Dealing with broken forearm and arm. 

That’s just for upper body… sucked I could barely do anything. 

Time under tension is how I’ve been able to build back muscle mass and stay lean. Resistance bands and body weight mostly. 

I looked at my disadvantages and realized facing adversity is a big advantage. 

It only sharpened me. 🤝🏾
I’m super grateful for life.
Pushing through all limitations. 🦾

Started adding weight to my lower body workouts now. 

What helped me get to this point was mobility, resistance, and stretch exercises.

Putting the titanium in my hip to work haha 😆
God knew I could stand the pressure when I was told I would never run again. I’m truly grateful for the progress.
Sometimes you just put on a hoodie and grind. 🤷🏾‍♂️
You shouldn’t give up. Fight for yourself and who you are. You’ve got to go through the worst times in life to get the best.
Don't let yourself fall under the pressures of life. Stay strong, and keep your mind in check.
